{"key":"post-10109288","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10109288</id>\n<content>Tests have shown that anything over about 2% Mg will impede fruiting performance.&amp;nbsp; Look for calcium carbonate or hydrated lime, and make sure it has low Mg percentage.&amp;nbsp; Avoid any lime with the word 'dolomite' associated with it.&amp;nbsp; Unless you're growing agaricus button mushrooms, a casing layer is not required with bulk substrates.&amp;nbsp; If you can't find the correct lime, I'd suggest growing on uncased manure or straw, etc.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10109349</next>\n<prev>10109275</prev>\n<first>10108901</first>\n<last>10109509</last>\n<when>1238940870</when>\n<utime>04/05/09 05:14 PM</utime>\n</post>"}